guicomponents

Class FPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • guicomponents.GComponent
      • guicomponents.FPanel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GConstants, Comparable<Object>, PConstants

    public class FPanel
extends GComponent
    A component that can be used to group GUI components that can be dragged, collapsed (leaves title tab only) and un-collapsed. When created the Panel is collapsed by default. To open the panel use setCollapsed(true); after creating it. Unlike all the other components the [x,y] coordinates do not represent the top-left corner of the control rather the top-left corner of the panel drawing surface (which is the bottom left corner of the tab)
    Author:
    Peter Lager
